## 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History — ✅ High

- Persist aggregates and hashes only; raw human labels and reviewer IDs are in-memory inputs, because durable raw review data changes the privacy and governance model.
- Link every report to run, candidate, dataset snapshot/hash, metric/version/direction, and threshold; free-floating reports would be easy to misinterpret.
- Make reports append-only and identical imports idempotent; no edit/delete/approval/promotion API exists in v0.3.0.
- Use bounded streamed raw request bodies instead of multipart uploads to avoid temporary-disk spooling and keep the 2 MiB ceiling enforceable.
- Require exact CSV/JSON content types to reduce cross-origin/simple-request mutation risk and accurately document the API.
- Keep case labels as verified display metadata excluded from canonical label hashes so CSV and JSON remain equivalent; escape formula-shaped CSV values.
- Normalize signed zero in scores/thresholds so semantically identical inputs have one identity.
- Hide calibration tools behind one optional switch within Results; adding a new navigation destination would distract from the primary evaluation flow.
- Label all current calibration reports `offline_statistical_evidence` and `production_validated=false`; no UI action can change that claim.
- Release only from the exact protected-main squash commit after independent main CI; use an annotated tag and immutable prerelease workflow.

